// Repo-root markdownlint-cli2 configuration.
//
// The repository follows a "one paragraph = one physical line" Markdown
// authoring convention documented in CLAUDE.md. This produces long single-line
// paragraphs by design. MD013 (line-length) MUST be disabled to avoid false
// positives on every paragraph.
//
// Other disabled rules cover legitimate documentation patterns:
//   - MD024 (no-duplicate-heading): multiple "## Configuration" / "## License"
//     sections appear across module READMEs; siblings_only is too lax in
//     markdownlint-cli2's default-config aliasing.
//   - MD033 (no-inline-html): shortcodes legitimately use inline HTML
//     (<details>, <br>, <img alt> in shields.io badges).
//   - MD041 (first-line-heading): files like CLAUDE.md and example fixtures
//     start with non-H1 content (front matter, code fences).
//   - modules/pwa/test/README.md and modules/pwa/test/IOS_MANUAL_MATRIX.md
//     are Phase 7 locked Playwright validation-matrix artifacts (paralleling
//     the .prettierignore exclusion). They use aligned Markdown tables where
//     long file-path links overflow header column widths; MD060 would flag
//     these legitimately but the test fixture documentation MUST NOT be
//     restyled to preserve the regression-free Phase 7 status.
//   - modules/images/test/fixture/content/ is deliberately hostile Markdown
//     test DATA (paralleling the .prettierignore exclusion): bare URLs inside
//     shortcode arguments, javascript: destinations, and attribute blocks
//     whose line structure is semantically load-bearing.
//   - test-results/ and playwright-report/ are Playwright-generated output
//     (error-context snapshots, HTML reports) that any module's test suite
//     can leave behind after a failed run; they are tool artifacts, never
//     authored content, and are excluded generically (paralleling the
//     .prettierignore patterns).
{
  "config": {
    "default": true,
    "MD013": false,
    "MD024": false,
    "MD033": false,
    "MD041": false,
  },
  "globs": ["**/*.md"],
  "ignores": [
    "node_modules/**",
    "**/node_modules/**",
    "**/public/**",
    "**/resources/**",
    ".code-review-graph/**",
    "modules/pwa/test/README.md",
    "modules/pwa/test/IOS_MANUAL_MATRIX.md",
    "modules/images/test/fixture/content/**",
    "**/test-results/**",
    "**/playwright-report/**",
  ],
}
